# FilmBox Backend Initialization Plan

This plan outlines the steps to set up the foundation for FilmBox, an AI-powered movie recommendation system.

## Proposed Changes

### Projct Structure
We will adopt a modular structure suitable for production-grade FastAPI applications, including dedicated directories for ML models and AI agents.

#### [NEW] Backend Structure
- `backend/app/main.py`: Entry point for the FastAPI application.
- `backend/app/core/`: Configuration and database setup.
- `backend/app/models/`: SQLAlchemy database models.
- `backend/app/schemas/`: Pydantic schemas for data validation.
- `backend/app/api/`: API route controllers.
- `backend/app/ml/`: Machine learning model implementations.
- `backend/app/agents/`: LangGraph/LangChain agent logic.

### Database Setup
- Using **SQLAlchemy** with **SQLite**.
- Configuration will use `pydantic-settings` to manage environment variables.

### Initial Endpoints
- A simple `GET /health` endpoint to verify the system is up.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Basic health-check test using `httpx`.

### Manual Verification
- Start the server using `uvicorn app.main:app --reload`.
- Access Swagger UI at `http://localhost:8000/docs`.
